items.title: Former Trump aide Steve Bannon pleads guilty in New York 'build the wall' case
items.description: Prosecutors had said Steve Bannon, who served briefly in the first Trump administration, swindled donors of a "build the wall" campaign.

items.title: Trump signs order pausing enforcement of foreign bribery ban
items.description: The Foreign Corrupt Practices Act became law in 1977. In 2024, the Department of Justice announced 24 cases related to the anti-bribery statute.

items.title: Supreme Court lawyer Tom Goldstein jailed as flight risk after cryptocurrency hiding claim
items.description: SCOTUSblog publisher Tom Goldstein was indicted in January on charges alleging he failed to declare millions of dollars in poker winnings.

items.title: Trump removes director of government ethics office
items.description: President Donald Trump removed David Huitema as director of the U.S. Office of Government Ethics, the agency said.
